%N A394606 Decimal expansion of the median of the distribution of distances between two points in a unit disk.
%C A394606 The median of the probability density function f(s) = (1/Pi) * 2*s*(2*theta(s) - sin(2*theta(s))), for 0 <= s <= 2, and 0 otherwise, where theta(s) = arccos(s/2).
%C A394606 The unique positive zero of 2*x^2*acos(x/2) + 2*asin(x/2) - x*sqrt(4 - x^2)*(x^2 + 2)/4 - Pi/2.
%H A394606 F. Garwood and J. C. Tanner, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/3610457">2800. On Note 2754: A Repeated Integral</a>, The Mathematical Gazette, Vol. 42, No. 342 (1958), pp. 292-293.
%e A394606 0.891290775025267601795706116907122985154537589398829...
%t A394606 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[2*x^2*ArcCos[x/2] + 2*ArcSin[x/2] - x*Sqrt[4 - x^2]*(x^2 + 2)/4 - Pi/2, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A394606 (PARI) solve(x = 1/2, 1, 2*x^2*acos(x/2) + 2*asin(x/2) - x*sqrt(4 - x^2)*(x^2 + 2)/4 - Pi/2)
%Y A394606 Cf. A093070 (mean), A102519, A394605 (mode), A394608 (square).
